org.lightsleep.entity

Annotation Type ColumnProperty


  • @Documented
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Repeatable(value=ColumnProperties.class)
 @Target(value=TYPE)
public @interface ColumnProperty
    Indicates the column name related to the field defined in superclass.

    This annotation is used to specify for fields defined in superclass. The specified contents also affects subclasses, but specifications in the subclass takes precedence. If you specify column="", the specification in the superclass is canceled.

    Java Example
      @ColumnProperty(property="name.first" column="firstName")
  @ColumnProperty(property="name.last" column="lastName")
   public class Person extends PersonBase {
    Groovy Example
      @ColumnProperties([
    @ColumnProperty(property='name.first' column='firstName'),
    @ColumnProperty(property='name.last' column='lastName')
  ])
  public class Person extends PersonBase {
    Generated SQL
     SELECT ..., firstName, lastName, ...
    Since:
    1.3.0
    Author:
    Masato Kokubo
    See Also:
    Column, ColumnProperties
